citeinfo.title: Phase 1 (Broad Scale) Forest Inventory Status

pubinfo.publish: Alberta Environment and Sustainable Resource Development, Government of Alberta

descript.abstract:
This dataset is produced for the Government of Alberta and is available to the general public. Please consult the Distribution Information of this metadata for the appropriate contact to acquire this dataset.
During and shortly after the Second World War the demand for lumber and wood products increased dramatically. This resulted in concern over lack of knowledge about the extent of the provincial forest resource, and led to fears that the timber supply could be easily depleted. The Phase 1, or Broad Scale, Forest Inventory was initiated in 1949 in response to these concerns. The inventory served as the information base to plan the management of Alberta's forest resource. The Phase 1 (Broad Scale) Forest Inventory included all publicly owned forested lands in the province except Indian lands, national parks and an area known as the Rocky Mountains Forest Reserve. Through aerial photo interpretation, land was classed according to vegetation cover as productive, potentially productive or non-productive.
The Phase 1 (Broad Scale) Forest Inventory generalized data, scanned images, reports, status map and index map are available from Alberta Environment and Sustainable Resource Development, Government of Alberta.
descript.purpose: The Phase 1 (Broad Scale) Forest Inventory was used to define lands suitable for agriculture, to determine timber harvest levels and plan forest protection and timber and industrial development. Cover types included crown density, height and tree species. Potentially productive and non-productive lands were classified. No age or site class associated with the polygons and a 65 hectare minimum polygon size was established.
descript.supplinf: All of the Phase 1 (Broad Scale) Forest Inventory scanned images are available in Portable Document Format (.pdf) and Tagged Image Format (.tif). The Phase 1 (Broad Scale) Forest Inventory background and methodology are described in the "Alberta Phase 3 Inventory An Overview", RIB# 874.

procstep.procdesc: The Phase 1 (Broad Scale) Forest Inventory Index feature class was intersected with the National Topographic Series (NTS) Grid 1:50 000 polygons and the mapsheet was captured in the NAME field. The new status map was cross-checked with the distribution list of Phase 1 (Broad Scale) Forest Inventory scanned images and adjusted to match.

dataqual.complete: The data are complete for the extent of the Phase 1 (Broad Scale) Forest Inventory area. There is additional mapping in mapsheet 83I04 that was not captured in the index map. Mapsheet 83G16 was included in the collection of scanned images but does not appear to contain any forest inventory data.
dataqual.logic: The feature class was checked for geometry errors and multipart polygons and repaired where necessary.
